The article is a statement by the President on the relationship between the United States and Burma. The President announces the nomination of the first U.S. Ambassador to Burma in 22 years, Derek Mitchell, and the easing of bans on the exportation of financial services and new investment in Burma. The United States is committed to supporting reformers, promoting economic development, and bringing Burma out of isolation. However, concerns remain about Burma's political system, treatment of minorities, detention of political prisoners, and relationship with North Korea. The United States will work to establish responsible investment and continue to hold those who commit human rights violations accountable. The article also highlights the ongoing support of the American people for the Burmese people and the recent economic and political reforms in Burma.